The paper deals with a problem of maximizing the total derived utility of a group of agents, which involves decision-making and optimization. This suggests that it could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms and models to solve the problem, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of formal specifications and tractability results, which could suggest it belongs to the Learning (cs.LG) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with group recommendation, which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
